org.gridgain.grid
Interface GridTaskContinuousMapper

public interface GridTaskContinuousMapper

Defines a mapper that can be used for asynchronous job sending.

Continuous mapper methods can be used right after it injected into a task. Mapper can not be used after GridTask.result(GridJobResult, List) method returned the GridJobResultPolicy.REDUCE policy. Also if GridTask.result(GridJobResult, List) method returned the GridJobResultPolicy.WAIT policy and all jobs are finished then task will go to reducing results and continuous mapper can not be used.

Note that whenever continuous mapper is used, GridTask.map(List, Object) method is allowed to return null in cased when at least one job has been sent prior to completing the GridTask.map(List, Object) method.

Task continuous mapper can be injected into a task using IoC (dependency injection) by attaching GridTaskContinuousMapperResource annotation to a field or a setter method inside of GridTask implementations as follows: 

 ...
 // This field will be injected with task continuous mapper.
 @GridTaskContinuousMapperResource
 private GridTaskContinuousMapper mapper;
 ...
or from a setter method: 
 // This setter method will be automatically called by the system
 // to set grid task continuous mapper.
 @GridTaskContinuousMapperResource
 void setSession(GridTaskContinuousMapper mapper) {
     this.mapper = mapper;
 }
